- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fragments of first-order logic over words and provides characterizations in terms of rankers. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with fragments of first-order logic over words and rankers, which are closely related to automata theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with the expressive power of different fragments of first-order logic, which is relevant to algorithmic complexity. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with the expressive power of different fragments of first-order logic, which is relevant to programming language semantics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the expressive power of different fragments of first-order logic, which is relevant to computational complexity theory.
